cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CC

The paper deals with sequential prediction strategies and their performance in the stochastic and worst-case settings. This makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Additionally, the development of new algorithms and methods for tuning learning rates suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of weights and hedging strategies may also indicate a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
